This paper is about action recognition from RGB-D data, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the evaluation of algorithms, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper provides recommendations for future research, which involves the use of new techniques and algorithms, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
